#X text 27 67 [snake~ split] expects a multichannel input and splits it into 2 output signals (mono or multichannel). The left outlets contains the first 'n' channels of the input. If 'n' is 0 (default) \, the left output is a signal of zeroes. Similarly \, if 'n' equals the amount of input channels \, the right outlet will be a signal of zeroes.;
